<p class="">That really does not quite do justice to Mr. Chamberlain, because the reason why he resigned was not because of any defeat in the House of Commons or that he could not gather support to continue, but because he felt that nothing short of a National Government could save the country.</p>                    <div class="hidden-md hidden-lg" style="padding-left: 0px;">
